commit.message:
Actions: Update more disc-based icons

Update/add some more disc-based icons: ISO, Copy, Video, fix symlinks for Brasero.

Devices: Update audio and data disc icons

Update disc-based device icons for data and audio.
These are used for both device icons, and as action
icons for some apps (like Xfburn).

Mimes: Use 'applications-other' for executables

Symlink the Mime icon `application-x-executable` to the
Category icon `applications-other`. It uses the same design
as what is used currently but has better contrast, looks better
on dark themes, and is used more widely in the theme to represent applications.

This will change the icon used for executable and binary mimes, as well as some
executable-related actions like "Create Launcher..." on Xfdesktop right click.

---

The `applications-other` icon is used for:
- "All Applications" in Whisker Menu
- "Launcher" Xfce panel plugin
- "Applications" when right clicking on Xfdesktop

The white-square-with-gear is also used for .desktop files on Xfdesktop
and thunar, and also more closely matches the icon used for other executable
mimes like Appimage, Debs, RPMs, etc.

Actions: Colorize send, clear, update some borders

Changed
- edit-clear (colorized, easier to see in dark themes)
- send-to (colorized, easier to see in dark themes)
          (use purple which already used for other send/share icons)
- user-publicshare (symlink to send-to, public folder icon at <24px will now match send-to)

Updated
- Arrows on most actions made rounded/smoother (same as upstream)
- Borders of many document action icons made semi-transparent, sharper on dark themes
- "Play" icon resized a bit to look more centered, match size of "Stop" icon better

Fixed
- gtk-revert-to-saved-rtl symlinked to document-revert-rtl (was symlinked to ltr)

Apps: Update software-properties icon

Use the new package style and globe/web icon.

Apps: New icon for Ubiquity (Xubuntu Installer)

Made larger than other icons to stand out a little better.
Also used the Xubuntu colors instead of elementary,
though they're pretty close, Xubuntu colors are a bit darker.

Apps: New Mousepad, Appfinder icons

New
- Xfce Appfinder
- Xfce Mousepad

Appfinder uses the `applications-all` and `applications-other` category
icons as base, hopefully tying to it the idea of "search for all applications".

Mousepad is based on the newer/future text editor icon from upstream elementary.

Both replace symlinks, which were used by many different apps/actions,
with unique icons. They're closer to the Xfce originals, and also use the
newer elementary gradients, colors, and rounded-square style.

Apps: Add Snap Store app icon (from Yaru)

Add Snap Store icon, sourced from the Yaru theme.
Missing sizes not found in Yaru created.

Closes #420

Apps: Add Xfce panel plugins, various fixes

Add symlinks/icons for the following Xfce panel plugins:
- Battery Monitor
- CPU Frequency
- Launcher (switched from mime to `applications-other` icon)
- PulseAudio

Fix:
- Clipman panel plugin now uses symbolic icon
  (icon slightly edited for symbolic use, renamed and moved to app folder)
- qBittorrent tray symbolic icon uses different name in some versions
- Removed extra hidden content from archive-manager (reduces size)
- Added back `stock_people` symlink, needed for User Setting (users-admin from gnome-system-tools)

Apps: Remove Chrome webapps

Chrome webapps are no longer supported on anything other than ChromeOS:

https://blog.chromium.org/2016/08/from-chrome-apps-to-web.html

The Youtube and Calendar icons could potentially be used as a base for
other app icons in the future but nothing I could think of currently.

Status: Add update-notifier icon

Add icon for update-notifier status notifier and dialog. A symlink
to `software-update-available` it should now match the update available
notification of Package Update Indicator.

Make 16px icons a little bigger to match other panel notification sizes.
(some of the border spills out but still looks better than before when in use)

Fix issue where 22px update "available" and "urgent" icons didn't match other sizes.

Actions: Update session icons

Updates arrow style, borders, gradients, and shadows to better match
elementary style. Should also make icons a little clearer and sharp looking.

Use green color for "safe" actions (Lock Screen and Switch User).
This should make them easier to see and look less like
disabled icons (previously they were a greyish color).

Closes #351

Animations: Add 16px connecting, symbolic folder

Add network "connecting" icons at 16px. This matches the previously
added VPN "connecting" icons, sourced from the Paper/Papirus icon theme.

Add `/animations/symbolic/` folder and moved symbolic icons there.

Fix one incorrectly colored VPN Connecting animation step.
Devices: Fix incorrectly sized USB icon at 22px

Status: New Wifi size for non-symbolic 16px icons

Update size for 16px non-symbolic Wifi.
This matches the size previously applied to the symbolic Wifi icons.
(addresses part of issue #152)

Colorize Wifi icons at 16px.

Remove 16px Wifi icons from "elementary-dark". The colorization means that
non-symbolic icons should be able to be used with light and dark themes.

Fixed issue where disconnected network used different icons for symbolic and
non-symbolic.

Apps: Remove symlinks which are no longer needed

Removed
- drakstats (Seems it was a part of old Mandrake/Mandriva, can't find modern mentions of it)
- file-roller (Gnome provides their own differently-named icon, so this wasn't being used anyway)
- gtklp* (not used, app makes its own xpm-based icons)
- nm-vpn-standalone-lock (removed in nm-applet)
  (https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/network-manager-applet/-/commit/4cf18cc)
- plugin-* (only used for ccsm, and we only provided 5 out of 60+ which looks
            bad/broken/incomplete. better they use their own all-matching icons.)
- system-installer (not used)
- system-software-installer (not used)

Renamed/Updated
- system-software-installer > system-software-install
  system-software-install is the correct freedesktop.org name.
  Resymlinked package icons (rpmdrake, synaptic, update-notifier, yumex > yumex-dnf)
- system-upgrade (deleted duplicate icon from /apps, kept in /actions)
Apps: Refresh system monitor / task manager icon

Apps: Add qBittorrent, refresh Dictionary

New
- qBittorrent

Refreshed
- Dictionary

Updated
- time-admin (rounded corners, semi-transparent borders, add missing sizes)
- wine (semi-transparent borders, add missing sizes)

For Reference: Used Noto Serif font for Dictionary

Apps: Add mpv, update and refresh others

A few redone to match newer elementary style, palette.
Should look a little better in dark themes with updated borders.
Improve some consistency between sizes.

New
- mpv

Updated/Refreshed
- menulibre
- multimedia-player (device icon, but used for some apps)
- preferences-desktop-font (based on upstream icon, replaced PNGs with SVGs)
- postscript/pdf viewer
- virtualbox
Mimes: Grid-align office icons

Status: Make symbolic wifi icon larger

New symbolic wifi icon to try to make size
of status / systray icons more consistent.

Addresses part of #152

Fix non-matching `open-menu` icon at 16px

Also update to semi-transparent borders for non-symbolic `open-menu` icons.

Closes #419

Move notification app icon to categories

The new notification icon was accepted upstream, with some icon tweaks.
This update adds those tweaks and renames and moves the icon to categories,
matching upstream.

Status: Make symbolic audio icons bigger

New symbolic audio icons to make size of status / systray icons more consistent.
Also uses the new strikethrough style for muted and blocking.

Addresses part of #152

Animations: Add VPN "connecting" icons at 16px

Add symbolic "connecting" icons seen when
trying to connect to a VPN.

Update non-symbolic icons to match, use blue color to
avoid needing monochrome icons for light and dark themes.

Icons from Papirus/Paper icon themes, updated AUTHORS with
licensing and links.

Mimes: Add Cue, deja vu, lossless audio

New
- Cue Sheet
- Lossless audio symlinks (APE/Monkey Audio, Wavpack)
- DejaVu (keep the pdf/document style, use purple color - closes #392)

Updated
- Changelog (Fix proportions at 96px, grid alignment at other sizes)
- Rename `extension` to `application-x-addon` (to match upstream), resymlink where needed

Apps: Add Calculator, Element, refresh others

New:
- Calculator (from upstream)
- Element (Matrix client)
- ibus-keyboard (symlink to devices/input-keyboard)

Updated:
- ibus-setup
- hexchat
- parole
- scim
- system-upgrade

Updates include using semi-transparent borders, more rounded borders,
adding sizes where missing, and making icons a little more uniform across sizes.

Fixed (updated to correct names):
- hexchat
- inkscape
